## 5. Rust Ecosystem for Audio ML

### 5.1 whisper-rs

**Version**: [0.15.1](https://crates.io/crates/whisper-rs) (Sep 2025). 183,918 total downloads, 27 versions published. Licensed under Unlicense.

**Maturity**: Actively maintained (7 releases in 2025). Primary repo moved to [Codeberg](https://codeberg.org/tazz4843/whisper-rs). 52% documentation coverage.

**API**:
```rust
let ctx = WhisperContext::new_with_params(model_path, params)?;
let mut state = ctx.create_state()?;
let params = FullParams::new(SamplingStrategy::Greedy { best_of: 1 });
state.full(params, &audio_data)?;
for i in 0..state.full_n_segments()? {
    let text = state.full_get_segment_text(i)?;
    let start = state.full_get_segment_t0(i)?;
    let end = state.full_get_segment_t1(i)?;
}
```

**Feature flags**: `cuda`, `hipblas`, `log_backend`, `tracing_backend`. Metal support is implicit through whisper.cpp's Metal backend.

**Alternative**: [whisper-cpp-plus](https://lib.rs/crates/whisper-cpp-plus) -- adds Silero VAD preprocessing for 2-3x speedup on audio with silence. Better safety guarantees (null checks, RAII cleanup, zero-copy).

### 5.2 Speaker Diarization in Rust

**No Rust-native diarization crates exist.** The ecosystem gap is significant.

### 5.3 Candle (HuggingFace)

[Candle](https://github.com/huggingface/candle) is HuggingFace's minimalist Rust ML framework. Supports CUDA, Metal, WASM. PyTorch-like API.

**For speaker embeddings**: No built-in ECAPA-TDNN or speaker embedding model. You would need to implement the architecture yourself or use ONNX export. The `candle_embed` crate exists for text embeddings, not audio.

**Assessment**: Promising but immature for audio/speaker tasks. Best for text/LLM inference currently.

### 5.4 Burn

[Burn](https://burn.dev/) v0.8.1 (2026) -- pure Rust ML framework. Backend-agnostic (CPU, CUDA, Metal, WGPU, WASM). Supports ONNX import and PyTorch weight loading.

